  <title>Computation using Sage</title>
  <p>
    As usual, this seems like it should be much easier using technology.
    Let's suppose <m>A=\begin{pmatrix}1 \amp  2 \\ 3 \amp  4 \end{pmatrix} , B=\begin{pmatrix}5 \amp  6 \\ 7 \amp  8 \end{pmatrix}</m>.
    Verify that:
    <md>
      <mrow>A+B\amp =\amp \begin{pmatrix}6 \amp  8 \\ 10 \amp  12 \end{pmatrix}</mrow>
      <mrow>AB\amp =\amp \begin{pmatrix}19 \amp  22 \\ 43 \amp  50 \end{pmatrix}</mrow>
      <mrow>BA\amp =\amp \begin{pmatrix}23 \amp  34 \\ 31 \amp  46 \end{pmatrix}</mrow>
    </md>
  </p>
